## Why This Is Asked
Tests the ability to design a zero-trust, per-tenant encryption and cross-account isolation architecture with advanced containment capabilities and hardware-level attestations.

## Key Concepts
- ABAC using tenant tags for granular cross-account access control
- Tenant-scoped CMKs with automated 90-day rotation and envelope encryption
- Nitro Enclaves attestations ensuring data-in-use protection via hardware isolation
- PrivateLink/VPC endpoints to eliminate public egress paths and enforce data residency
- 60-second containment workflow: automatic credential revocation, CMK rotation, and tenant quarantine
- Immutable auditing: CloudTrail with organizational trails, S3 Object Lock for WORM compliance, and Lake Formation for fine-grained data access logging

## Code Example
```javascript
// Example policy for tenant-scoped ABAC access
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::${AccountId}:role/EMR-Spark-Worker"
      },
      "Action": [
        "kms:Decrypt",
        "kms:GenerateDataKey"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:kms:*:*:key/tenant-${TenantId}-*",
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "aws:PrincipalTag/tenant-id": "${TenantId}"
        },
        "Bool": {
          "aws:SecureTransport": "true"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to implement tenant isolation with least privilege, plus rapid containment using AWS-native controls. It also covers S3 prefix scoping, per-tenant KMS keys, CloudTrail data events, and automated revocation.

## Key Concepts
- Least privilege IAM for Lambda and prefix-scoped S3 access
- S3 bucket policies with bucket-level and object-prefix constraints
- Per-tenant KMS keys and rotation
- CloudTrail Data Events for S3 access
- EventBridge-based containment workflow (60s)

## Code Example
```javascript
// IAM policy snippet for Lambda role
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["s3:GetObject","s3:ListBucket"],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::data-lake",
        "arn:aws:s3:::data-lake/tenant-id-${aws:PrincipalTag tenantId}/*"
      ],
      "Condition": {
        "StringLike": {"s3:prefix": "tenant-id-*"}
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

